she is that Battle's "sudden stardom" (20 years is sudden?) has ill-prepared 
her for the demands of the Met. She then goes on to whine about how sad she is 
to find that an "Olympian" like Battle could be petty. Who cares what Battle 
(or Krisel, for that matter) does offstage? We love Battle for her dedication 
to art, her flawlessly professional performances, her keen insight and 
intuition, and her enormous talent. What facts about Battle has Krisel offered 
that could discredit any of these?  
</P>
