<P>
PERSONAL HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ASSOCIATED PRESS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Jordan's name is everywhere. There are high-top sneakers, T-shirts, 
posters, basketballs.And now's there's even Air Jordan bacteria. 
</P>
<P>
 Sound gross? Not at all, Dr. Stanford Shulman tells 3-2-1-Contact magazine. 
He's the person who named a new strain of salmonella after the b-ball star. 
(Salmonella bacteria causes upset stomachs.) 
</P>
<P>
 Shulman didn't mean it as an insult. He says he named the strain he discovered 
Salmonella mjordan because he's a big fan of Jordan. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have a huge stand-up poster of him in my office," Shulman said. "Believe 
me, I meant for this to be a high honor." 
