NHL ROUNDUP; NEELY'S 50TH GOAL IN 44TH GAME PUTS HIM IN FAST COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cam Neely tied Mario Lemieux in becoming the second-fastest player in NHL 
history to reach the 50-goal mark, leading the Boston Bruins to a 6-3 victory 
over the Washington Capitals Monday night at Boston. 
</P>
<P>
 Neely scored his league-leading 49th and 50th goals in only his 44th game of 
the season as the Bruins extended their unbeaten streak to seven games at 
6-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Wayne Gretzky scored 50 goals in 39 games during the 1981-82 season and 42 
games in 1983-84. Lemieux reached 50 in 44 games during the 1988-89 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Detroit 6, New York Rangers 3 -- Sergei Fedorov had a goal and two assists as 
the Red Wings scored the last four goals to win at New York. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Louis 3, Toronto 2 -- Newcomer Petr Nedved assisted on two of Steve 
Duchesne's three goals as the Blues recorded their first regular-season victory 
in Toronto's Maple Leaf Gardens in more than three years. 
