<TEXT>
<P>
 Emeka Okenwa had 22 points and nine rebounds to lead The Master's College of 
Newhall to a 93-80 victory over Biola in the championship game of the NAIA Far 
West Region Independents men's basketball tournament at Concordia University in 
Irvine Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fourth in a row for Master's (28-4), its 18th in the last 
19 games, and propelled the Mustangs into the 32-team NAIA Division I 
tournament at Oral Roberts University in Tulsa for the first time.The 
tournament will be held from March 15-21. 
</P>
