<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY ATHLETE OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Finneran 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Forward 
</P>
<P>
 Not much separates twin brothers Brad and Brian Finneran. Football standouts, 
they each accepted offers to play at Villanova next season.Strong students, 
their grade-point averages are within a tenth of a point of each other. They 
each have taken turns leading the Eagle basketball team. But Saturday in the 
Southern Section Division III-AA title game against Servite, Brad supplied most 
of the offense. He scored a game-high 26 points on 11-for-19 shooting from the 
field and also had six rebounds three steals and two assists. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Rudy Gomez, Mater Dei, scored two goals in a 4-1 victory over Esperanza in 
the Division II soccer title game. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jon Surface, Pacifica, had 23 points and five rebounds in a 63-49 victory 
over San Dimas in the Division III-A title game. 
</P>
<P>
 * Shane Valdez, Calvary Chapel, won the State wrestling title at 119 pounds, 
leading the Eagles to their second consecutive team title. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jaret Wright, Katella, pitched a no-hitter with 11 strikeouts and hit two 
home runs and had four RBIs in a 7-1 victory over Laguna Hills. 
</P>
