<P>
 Kohler's business card lists him as vice president of investments and already 
he sees his team paying dividends. In his first year at Laguna Beach, Kohler 
takes over for Donn Munsell, who coached the Artists for two years. Kohler has 
some solid stock in McDonald, a first-team all-league second baseman. McDonald 
hit .374 with two home runs in his junior year and is an all-around athlete who 
makes few fielding errors. Sauers seems to be drawing the most interest, as 
UCLA, Army and Louisville are among the schools looking to invest in his 
services. Sauers was a second-team all-league selection last season after 
hitting .311 with five home runs and 27 runs batted in. Kohler is particularly 
impressed with his young team's attitude and thinks it can improve on its 
fifth-place league standing last year. The Artists have finished with identical 
10-15 overall records the past two years, but lost two more games in league 
last season than in 1992. Look for the Artists to get an immediate test in the 
Pacific Coast League when they open league play at Laguna Hills on March 18 and 
then travel to Trabuco Hills for their next game March 22. 
</P>
