<P>
 Seven returning starters make up the core of Trabuco Hills' squad, which 
finished third behind Laguna Hills and Century last season. Brouwer begins his 
third season with the Mustangs and believes his team will be right in the 
middle of the league race. Cervantes is a big, power-hitting first baseman who 
is headed for USC after his all-league junior year. Anderson and Poe also were 
second-team picks. Rechner and Beckham should give the Mustangs one of the 
fastest outfield units in the county. Pitching will be a question mark for 
Trabuco Hills, which lost staff ace Carey Smith to graduation. Sperling and 
Pintsak will have to develop and progress if the Mustangs are going to make a 
run at Laguna Hills. The Mustangs have a difficult nonleague schedule that 
begins with the Newport Elks tournament. Participating in the tournament are 
teams such as Capistrano Valley and Mater Dei. The Mustangs open the tournament 
against Orange, the defending Century League champion. League play begins with 
a trip to Century on March 18. 
