behind him and was a first-team all-league pick. Johnson, McDermott, Hills, 
Miller and Milo, the lone left-hander, all got starts on the mound for the 
Hawks last season. Also, several younger players have stepped up from the lower 
levels and should push for playing time. Throw in the Hawks' good defense and 
team speed, and this could be Laguna Hills' best team ever. 
