<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN PLEADS GUILTY TO KILLING 5 IN HIS FAMILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who shot to death five members of his family pleaded guilty but mentally 
ill Monday to five counts of murder. 
</P>
<P>
 George Hardebeck faces up to 300 years in prison when he is sentenced April 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the plea, Hardebeck will be able to receive treatment for mental illness 
while in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 State police said Hardebeck, 32, confessed to killing his 73-year-old mother, 
two brothers, his sister and her huband after a heated argument at the family 
farm. 
</P>
