<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; COUNCIL CONSIDERING HEALTH CLUB ORDINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Burbank City Council tonight will consider regulating health clubs with an 
ordinance requiring at least a $75,000 bond to ensure that membership fees can 
be returned if a club closes. 
</P>
<P>
 Checking the backgrounds of club owners is another element of the ordinance 
under consideration. If approved, the new ordinance would go into effect in 30 
days. In the meantime, a moratorium on issuing permits for health clubs that 
went into effect in December would be extended. 
</P>
<P>
 The council is also considering a permit fee of at least $100 for clubs. ED 
BOND 
