<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MAN SOUGHT IN DISAPPEARANCE OF 3-YEAR-OLD BOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are searching for a man who disappeared with his 
girlfriend's 3-year-old grandson and her check for $2,300 she gave him to 
deposit more than one week ago, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ralph Courtney Sykes, 39, left girlfriend Beverly Ann Smith's Newhall home 
last Tuesday, supposedly headed for a bank to deposit a Federal Emergency 
Management Agency check for $2,300 into her account, said Deputy Rich Erickson 
of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Montice Kaylon Williams, 3, was with Sykes when he drove off in Smith's 
two-door, gray 1976 Oldsmobile Starfire, which bears a California license plate 
number of 868-RVA, Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, 41, fears for her grandson's safety because she said that Sykes is a 
cocaine addict, and may have taken the boy and the check to South-Central Los 
Angeles where he apparently has connections to obtain drugs, Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith reported her grandson missing and her car stolen last week, Erickson 
said. She has discussed the disappearance of the check with detectives, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sykes is African American, 5-feet-9 and weighs about 148 pounds. Montice has 
brown hair and brown eyes, is about 3 feet tall and weighs about 35 pounds. He 
was wearing a white T-shirt, a gray sweat shirt, a black jacket and black 
tennis shoes, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
