<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: BOGOTA; POLLS IN BLOODY BOGOTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amid a wave of violence, Colombians will vote Sunday for new legislators in 
elections that could shed light on presidential races later this year. 
</P>
<P>
 All 100 senators and 163 members of the House of Representatives will be 
chosen. Election-watchers will look to the voting to gauge the strength of 
Colombia's two major political parties, the Liberals and the Conservatives, in 
anticipation of presidential elections on May 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Leftist guerrillas, in an effort to disrupt the elections and seize territory, 
have stepped up attacks recently and have threatened American targets. 
</P>
