<P>
 Computer Sciences Corp. Wins Navy Contract: The El Segundo-based company said 
it has been awarded a five-year, $97.5 million contract to supply weapons 
systems engineering and software support to the Navy. It said the work will be 
done by its Integrated Systems Division at bases in Pascagoula, Miss., and 
Bath, Me. CSC has $2.5 billion in annual revenue and employs 28,500 people at 
450 offices in the United States, Europe and Australia. 
</P>
