<TEXT>
<P>
 Fed Governor Sees Stable Short-Term Rates: U.S. short-term interest rates will 
probably remain near 3% this year, Federal Reserve Board Gov. Lawrence Lindsey 
said.His remarks implied that the Fed may not push short-term interest rates 
sharply higher this year. On Feb. 4, Fed Chairman Alan Greenspan announced the 
board was boosting short-term rates on loans among banks to head off inflation. 
The so-called federal funds rate rose to 3.75% from 3%. Lindsey told a 
Baltimore meeting of the Commercial Finance Assn. that he concurs with 
forecasts that the U.S. output of goods and services, retail price hikes and 
short-term rates will all be about 3% this year. 
