<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: 4TH-QUARTER PROFITS FALL 16% AT CHEESECAKE FACTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cheesecake Factory Inc., the Calabasas-based chain of upscale restaurants, 
said its fourth-quarter profit fell 16% from a year earlier because of higher 
food and labor expenses and before opening costs at a new Atlanta outlet. 
</P>
<P>
 The company earned $1.28 million for the quarter that ended Jan. 2, compared 
with a profit of $1.53 million in the comparable period a year earlier.After 
news of the lower-than-expected earnings, the company's stock fell $3.625 a 
share, to $29.375, on unusually heavy trading last Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue for the latest quarter from restaurant and bakery sales surged 46% to 
$18.4 million, from $12.6 million a year earlier. Sales at restaurants open at 
least a year rose 4% in the latest quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year that ended Jan. 2, the Cheesecake Factory posted a profit 
of $4.75 million, up 13% from the previous fiscal year. Revenue for the latest 
fiscal year surged 13% to $55.7 million, from $42.9 million. 
</P>
