REGIONAL EARNINGS: MRV TRIPLES ITS PROFIT IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MRV Communications Inc., a Chatsworth manufacturer of semiconductor laser 
diodes and fiber-optic products used in communications networks, reported sharp 
increases in earnings and revenues for its fourth quarter and the year ended 
Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth quarter, MRV earned $317,000, up from the $95,000 in net income 
it reported a year ago. Its quarterly revenue grew by 89%, from $1.27 million 
to $2.39 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, the company had a profit of $839,000, a 50% gain from its 
$560,000 in earnings a year before. Its revenue rose 68%, from $4.42 million to 
$7.43 million. 
</P>
<P>
 MRV said the improved results reflected continued demand for, and reliance on, 
fiber-optic technology in communications markets. 
