<P>
RESTRUCTURED UNILAB REPORTS PROFITS FOR 4TH QUARTER, '93 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unilab Corp., a Tarzana-based operator of clinical laboratories that completed 
a restructuring in November, reported profits for its fourth quarter and year 
ended Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's fourth-quarter profit was $1.1 million, in contrast with a 
year-earlier loss of $90.4 million.Its quarterly revenue fell 26%, to $37.7 
million from $50.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, Unilab's profit was $6.51 million, in contrast with a loss of 
$98 million in 1992. Its annual revenue fell 3%, to $207.4 million from $213.9 
million. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1993 results include a one-time, pretax charge of $5.6 million related to 
the company's settlement of government claims. 
</P>
<P>
 Included in the 1992 results were $90.4 million in non-recurring charges from 
the write-off of intangible assets and goodwill. 
