<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: LTC PROPOSES TO SELL COMMON STOCK SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LTC Properties Inc., an Oxnard-based real estate investment trust, has 
proposed to sell up to 4.6 million shares of common stock to fund $35 million 
in investment commitments, repay $11 million in debt and make additional 
investments. 
</P>
<P>
 LTC invests in long-term nursing facilities nationwide, mainly by making 
mortgage loans secured by the properties. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said $32 million of the investments to be funded by the stock sale 
will be in mortgages while $3 million will be in sale-lease back deals. 
</P>
<P>
 LTC expects to receive an average annual yield of 10.8% on the loans, which 
will be secured by 17 nursing homes in eight states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
