<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: FIRM SIGNS INTENT LETTER TO ACQUIRE LIGHTWAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A West Los Angeles company, Metro Wireless Interactive Corp., says it has 
signed a letter of intent to acquire Simi Valley-based Lightwave Products Inc., 
producer of an interactive system that allows teleconferencing between computer 
users. 
</P>
<P>
 The system is currently being used by the FBI, the Defense Department and 
several other government agencies and companies, Metro said. 
</P>
<P>
 Amos Lewis, Lightwave's president, will remain as head of the Simi Valley firm 
under a long-term contract and will also receive an undisclosed amount of Metro 
shares, the announcement added. 
</P>
<P>
 The value of the transaction was not disclosed. 
</P>
