<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: SIEMENS FINISHES SOLAR ELECTRIFICATION PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo-based Siemens Solar Industries has completed what it calls the 
largest solar home electrification project in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, which will provide photovoltaic or solar power to 108 homes in 
the Sacramento area, was installed by Siemens in cooperation with the 
Sacramento Municipal Utility District. 
</P>
<P>
 The district is seeking clean, renewable power sources that will minimize the 
so-called greenhouse effect. 
</P>
<P>
 The project uses Siemens M55 solar panels that generate a total of 400 
kilowatts of electricity. Each home in the project is equipped with solar 
panels that will generate power throughout the grid. 
</P>
<P>
 Siemens, the world's largest supplier of solar products, hopes to install 
similar systems worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
