<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHISTLER'S RESTORED 'ARRANGEMENT' AT GETTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Arrangement in Black: Pablo de Sarasate," a recently restored painting by 
James Abbott McNeill Whistler, is on view at the J. Paul Getty Museum until the 
end of May. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1884 portrait of the internationally renowned violinist and composer 
belongs to the Carnegie Museum of Art in Pittsburgh, which loaned the work to 
the museum in Malibu in exchange for conservation services. 
</P>
<P>
 Prior to putting the painting on display, Getty conservators removed a 
confusing array of paint applied by earlier restorers and revealed Whistler's 
subtle variations of light and shade. 
</P>
