<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: SANTIAGO; LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chile's President-elect Eduardo Frei, a Christian Democrat, will take office 
Friday, receiving the same presidential sash used in his father's inauguration 
30 years ago.Frei's late father, also named Eduardo, was president from 1964 
through 1970. 
</P>
<P>
 The son, 51, will succeed President Patricio Aylwin, also a Christian 
Democrat. Frei won election in December to serve as the second civilian 
president since Gen. Augusto Pinochet relinquished power in 1990, ending a 
lengthy period of military rule. 
</P>
