<P>
17-YEAR-OLD IS SHOT, FRIEND BEATEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old Cypress youth was shot and wounded and his friend was beaten 
after a group of suspected gang members asked them their gang affiliation 
outside a video arcade late Sunday evening, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 The attack occurred outside the Western Arcade about 11 p.m., said Cypress 
Police Lt. Jim Weuve. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not release the victims' names because they are minors. Weuve said 
police are searching for three to 10 males, ages 17 to 18, in connection with 
the attack.  
</P>
<P>
